                                                                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13176906" author="raminder" created="Thu, 29 Dec 2011 00:22:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is the known issue with Commons Validator &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/VALIDATOR-248&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/VALIDATOR-248&lt;/a&gt;. Issue is fixed in 1.4.0-SNAPSHOT. Is it fine to update to snapshot version or wait for the release?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;For reference about fix.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/commons/proper/validator/trunk/src/test/java/org/apache/commons/validator/routines/UrlValidatorTest.java?view=markup&amp;amp;pathrev=595020&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://svn.apache.org/viewvc/commons/proper/validator/trunk/src/test/java/org/apache/commons/validator/routines/UrlValidatorTest.java?view=markup&amp;amp;pathrev=595020&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13177253" author="raminder" created="Thu, 29 Dec 2011 16:35:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached a patch for localhost validation. I did not apply the changes as Commons validator have snapshot version. I added validation test method if someone need to add particular validation in future.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13178473" author="jashajoachimsthal" created="Mon, 2 Jan 2012 17:39:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Unfortunately we cannot release with a SNAPSHOT dependency. We can ask on the commons mailinglist if there are plans to release validator 1.4 soon (there was a beta1 last summer but no follow up). Otherwise we either have to find an alternative validator or change our demo gadgets from localhost to 127.0.0.1.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Something different: we cannot legally use your patch because you haven&apos;t clicked the radio button &quot;Grant license to ASF for inclusion in ASF works (as per the Apache License &#167;5)&quot; when attaching the patch&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13178478" author="raminder" created="Mon, 2 Jan 2012 17:49:09 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Thanks Jasha to pointing out i need not clicked grant button. I never noticed that. i will resubmit the patch. I was almost aware of the fact that we can&apos;t use the snapshot so i did not commit to the trunk and submitted a patch as if someone wants the change. I will email on the commons validator dev about their plans.  &lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13178483" author="jashajoachimsthal" created="Mon, 2 Jan 2012 17:56:15 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;That button is very easy to overlook &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/sad.png&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt; If someone allows the patch for inclusion you can see the feather logo between the file icon and the file name.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13178489" author="raminder" created="Mon, 2 Jan 2012 18:04:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;with ASF grant&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13202176" author="jashajoachimsthal" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 08:52:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Commons validator 1.4.0 has been released so we should check if we can upgrade.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;http://announce.markmail.org/thread/nndvgkitsqjlo5e7&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://announce.markmail.org/thread/nndvgkitsqjlo5e7&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13202422" author="raminder" created="Tue, 7 Feb 2012 14:28:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;i will try to update the validator today. Thanks Jasha.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13203264" author="raminder" created="Wed, 8 Feb 2012 04:20:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;updated common validator to 1.4.0&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13214751" author="mfranklin" created="Thu, 23 Feb 2012 14:41:14 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Closing old resolved issues&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
